
test_dma: User container to test the DMA

Message: COPY|FILL|READ|GETBUF [SRC | FILL_DATA] DST DATALEN
  SRC:       Source data address (copy)
  FILL_DATA: Fill data value (fill)
  DST:       Destination address
  DATALEN:   Data length in bytes

All the data is in little endian format (input and output).

Load the container and see usage in logs:
$ mwtest.py -c100 run test_dma.img
$ cmtest log

To copy 32 bytes of data from one address (0x01032D78) to another (0x40000000):
$ cmtest cmd -f100 COPY 00000040 782D0301 20000000
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 0 bytes OK

To fill 64 bytes of a memory address (0x40000000) with some value (0x11223344):
$ cmtest cmd -f100 FILL 00000040 33442211 40000000
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 0 bytes OK

To read 16 bytes from a memory address (0x01032D78):
$ cmtest cmd -f100 READ 782D0301 10000000
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 16 bytes OK
00000000: 44 33 22 11 44 33 22 11  44 33 22 11 44 33 22 11  |D3".D3".D3".D3".|

To get the container SRAM buffer address:
$ cmtest cmd -f100 GETBUF
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 4 bytes OK
00000000: 78 2d 03 01                                       |x-..|

To unload container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 unload
